Package com.company.rest.products.model.liteproduct

Class LiteProduct

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.company.rest.products.model.liteproduct.LiteProduct
  • @Entity
public class LiteProduct
extends java.lang.Object
    LiteProduct is a cached version of products, with only a subset of the fields a user might provide. A local database of such instances are made, and the String id that the client provides is the primary key for those instances.
    See Also:
    LiteProductRepository

      • buildLiteProductFromPostAndPutRequests

        public static LiteProduct buildLiteProductFromPostAndPutRequests​(@NonNull
                                                                 @NonNull ProductUpsertRequestBody putRequest,
                                                                 @NonNull
                                                                 @NonNull ProductUpsertRequestBody postRequest)
        Build a LiteProduct instance out of two ProductUpsertRequestBody instances, one for a PUT request and another for its originating POST. Since UPDATE requests (PUT, PATCH) are allowed to change as many fields as they can, some of the crucial fields for the creation of a LiteProduct might be null. So we need both requests to build a LiteProduct instance.
        Parameters:
        putRequest - A ProductUpsertRequestBody instance corresponding to a PUT request.
        postRequest - A ProductUpsertRequestBody instance corresponding to the POST request that putRequest comes after.
        Returns:
        An instance of this.
